(946, '_transient_dash_4077549d03da2e451c8b5f002294ff51', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''https://wordpress.org/news/2015/07/wordpress-4-2-3/''>WordPress 4.2.3 Security and Maintenance Release</a> <span class="rss-date">July 23, 2015</span><div class="rssSummary">WordPress 4.2.3 is now available. This is a critical security release for all previous versions and we strongly encourage you to update your sites immediately. WordPress versions 4.2.2 and earlier are affected by a critical cross-site scripting vulnerability, which could allow anonymous users to compromise a site. This was reported by Jon Cave of the [&hellip;]</div></li></ul></div><div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wptavern.com/wordpress-custom-post-type-ui-plugin-passes-1-million-downloads''>WPTavern: WordPress Custom Post Type UI Plugin Passes 1 Million Downloads</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wptavern.com/wordpress-4-3-moves-customize-to-its-own-top-level-menu-in-the-admin-bar''>WPTavern: WordPress 4.3 Moves Customize to Its Own Top-level Menu in the Admin Bar</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wptavern.com/how-and-when-mullenweg-learned-thesis-changed-back-to-a-proprietary-license''>WPTavern: How and When Mullenweg Learned Thesis Changed Back to a Proprietary License</a></li></ul></div><div class="rss-widget"><ul><li class=''dashboard-news-plugin''><span>Popular Plugin:</span> <a href=''https://wordpress.org/plugins/mailchimp-for-wp/'' class=''dashboard-news-plugin-link''>MailChimp for WordPress</a>&nbsp;<span>(<a href=''plugin-install.php?tab=plugin-information&amp;plugin=mailchimp-for-wp&amp;_wpnonce=81e338cb76&amp;TB_iframe=true&amp;width=600&amp;height=800'' class=''thickbox'' title=''MailChimp for WordPress''>Install</a>)</span></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
