(70, 1, '2015-04-06 04:09:12', '2015-04-06 04:09:12', 'You know when you <img class="size-medium wp-image-71 alignleft" src="http://www.spiritmama.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/its-ok-to-loose-your-shyt-300x251.png" alt="its ok to loose your shyt" width="300" height="251" />have one of those days when you keep losing your shyt..One child has a cold, the other is teething, you''ve been up since 5.30am and to top it off you get a phone call saying ‘honey, I''m going to be late tonight’ - urgh.\r\n\r\nYou take a deep breath, look at the clock and think “great 6 ½ hours to go”..\r\nAlong rolls witching hour, you know, that time between 5-6 when the kids go a little nuts, you go a little nuts and everyone is tired and hungry?\r\n\r\nWell, while I''m feeding Indi a dinner she keeps refusing and Ollie is tipping water all over the floor I think to my increasingly stressed self ‘what can I be learning here’ ‘where is my resistance to this moment?’\r\n\r\nI try to smile calmly and be present as I''m faced with more food refusal in-between yelling at Ollie to ‘stop tipping water all over the floor!’ I walk out of the room to run the bath, deep breath in…nothing.\r\n\r\nNo spiritual tools are helping me right now. Why does that happen? Where are they when you need them?\r\n\r\nIs it only in quiet moments of peace do we contemplate our truth and divinity? Why not in the midst of looking after two kids at dinner time!\r\n\r\nTo make my point, it wasn''t until later that night while I was picking bits of grated cheese off the floor that I realised ‘hey, it’s ok to lose your shyt sometimes, being a mum is <u>hard work’</u>\r\n\r\n‘Be a little kinder to yourself here’. And BINGO! That’s it! That was my lesson that arose out of all this chaos.\r\n\r\nI contemplated “Being a little kinder to myself. And realised I’m doing a pretty amazing job here given the circumstances” and with that my mama guilt lifted and I ran myself a bath.\r\n\r\nHow have you been a little kinder to yourself today?', '''Its ok to sometimes lose your shyt''', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'its-ok-to-sometimes-lose-your-shyt', '', '', '2015-07-22 04:13:11', '2015-07-22 04:13:11', '', 0, 'http://www.spiritmama.com.au/?p=70', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(71, 1, '2015-07-21 04:05:48', '2015-07-21 04:05:48', '', 'its ok to loose your shyt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'its-ok-to-loose-your-shyt', '', '', '2015-07-21 04:05:48', '2015-07-21 04:05:48', '', 70, 'http://www.spiritmama.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/its-ok-to-loose-your-shyt.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(72, 1, '2015-07-21 04:07:16', '2015-07-21 04:07:16', 'You know when you have one of those days when you keep losing your shyt..One child has a cold, the other is teething, you''ve been up since 5.30am and to top it off you get a phone call saying ‘honey, I''m going to be late tonight’ - urgh.\r\n\r\nYou take a deep breath, look at the clock and think “great 6 ½ hours to go”..\r\n<img class="size-medium wp-image-71 aligncenter" src="http://www.spiritmama.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/its-ok-to-loose-your-shyt-300x251.png" alt="its ok to loose your shyt" width="300" height="251" />Along rolls witching hour, you know, that time between 5-6 when the kids go a little nuts, you go a little nuts and everyone is tired and hungry?\r\n\r\nWell, while I''m feeding Indi a dinner she keeps refusing and Ollie is tipping water all over the floor I think to my increasingly stressed self ‘what can I be learning here’ ‘where is my resistance to this moment?’\r\n\r\nI try to smile calmly and be present as I''m faced with more food refusal in-between yelling at Ollie to ‘stop tipping water all over the floor!’ I walk out of the room to run the bath, deep breath in…nothing.\r\n\r\nNo spiritual tools are helping me right now. Why does that happen? Where are they when you need them?\r\n\r\nIs it only in quiet moments of peace do we contemplate our truth and divinity? Why not in the midst of looking after two kids at dinner time!\r\n\r\nTo make my point, it wasn''t until later that night while I was picking bits of grated cheese off the floor that I realised ‘hey, it’s ok to lose your shyt sometimes, being a mum is <u>hard work’</u>\r\n\r\n‘Be a little kinder to yourself here’. And BINGO! That’s it! That was my lesson that arose out of all this chaos.\r\n\r\nI contemplated “Being a little kinder to myself. And realised I’m doing a pretty amazing job here given the circumstances” and with that my mama guilt lifted and I ran myself a bath.\r\n\r\nHow have you been a little kinder to yourself today?', '''Its ok to sometimes lose your shyt''', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '70-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-21 04:07:16', '2015-07-21 04:07:16', '', 70, 'http://www.spiritmama.com.au/?p=72', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(73, 1, '2015-07-21 04:08:04', '2015-07-21 04:08:04', 'You know when you <img class="size-medium wp-image-71 alignleft" src="http://www.spiritmama.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/its-ok-to-loose-your-shyt-300x251.png" alt="its ok to loose your shyt" width="300" height="251" />have one of those days when you keep losing your shyt..One child has a cold, the other is teething, you''ve been up since 5.30am and to top it off you get a phone call saying ‘honey, I''m going to be late tonight’ - urgh.\r\n\r\nYou take a deep breath, look at the clock and think “great 6 ½ hours to go”..\r\nAlong rolls witching hour, you know, that time between 5-6 when the kids go a little nuts, you go a little nuts and everyone is tired and hungry?\r\n\r\nWell, while I''m feeding Indi a dinner she keeps refusing and Ollie is tipping water all over the floor I think to my increasingly stressed self ‘what can I be learning here’ ‘where is my resistance to this moment?’\r\n\r\nI try to smile calmly and be present as I''m faced with more food refusal in-between yelling at Ollie to ‘stop tipping water all over the floor!’ I walk out of the room to run the bath, deep breath in…nothing.\r\n\r\nNo spiritual tools are helping me right now. Why does that happen? Where are they when you need them?\r\n\r\nIs it only in quiet moments of peace do we contemplate our truth and divinity? Why not in the midst of looking after two kids at dinner time!\r\n\r\nTo make my point, it wasn''t until later that night while I was picking bits of grated cheese off the floor that I realised ‘hey, it’s ok to lose your shyt sometimes, being a mum is <u>hard work’</u>\r\n\r\n‘Be a little kinder to yourself here’. And BINGO! That’s it! That was my lesson that arose out of all this chaos.\r\n\r\nI contemplated “Being a little kinder to myself. And realised I’m doing a pretty amazing job here given the circumstances” and with that my mama guilt lifted and I ran myself a bath.\r\n\r\nHow have you been a little kinder to yourself today?', '''Its ok to sometimes lose your shyt''', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '70-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-21 04:08:04', '2015-07-21 04:08:04', '', 70, 'http://www.spiritmama.com.au/?p=73', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(74, 1, '2015-02-04 04:13:53', '2015-02-04 04:13:53', 'It’s been a month now since my last breastfeed. Well I couldn''t even call it a feed; there wasn''t much in it for her. But it was a decision I put a lot of stress on myself over. Dreading the pangs of missing that close bond and interaction, feeling teary at the sight of seeing another mum and bub in that close embrace. As her feeds dropped<a href="http://www.spiritmama.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/1.png"><img class="alignright wp-image-75 size-medium" src="http://www.spiritmama.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/1-300x251.png" alt="1" width="300" height="251" /></a> one by one I really made an effort to enjoy every feed, be present with her and soak up the experience as much as I could. Here are somethings they <u>don’t </u>tell you that happen when you finish breastfeeding;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You get quite hormonal for like 4 frickin weeks</li>\r\n	<li>It takes about 6 weeks for your boobs to ‘go down’</li>\r\n	<li>You may be a smaller bra size than what you were before you got pregnant and some lucky ones and go up!</li>\r\n	<li>Your boobs will be a bit saggy so you’ll probably never want to go braless or topless again.</li>\r\n	<li>You may stare a bit too long at kid free women and think “how are they so high and perky?”</li>\r\n	<li>You do feel a bit more ‘normal’ or more like your old self again (just an older, more tired version)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYou know what? Once it was done, I didn’t really look back. I do wish things could have been different breastfeeding Indi this time around but things are what they are. There''s always more to look forward to..new ''non-maternity'' bras with skinny straps!, new swimmers and tops that don’t need instant boob access..\r\n\r\nSo all in all, yes I miss that closeness we shared while breastfeeding but I will cherish what we had and keep those memories close to my heart.', 'When breastfeeding comes to an end', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'when-breastfeeding-comes-to-an-end', '', '', '2015-07-22 04:08:21', '2015-07-22 04:08:21', '', 0, 'http://www.spiritmama.com.au/?p=74', 0, 'post', '', 0),
