'', '2015-07-21 04:13:53', '2015-07-21 04:13:53', '', 74, 'http://www.spiritmama.com.au/?p=77', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(78, 1, '2014-12-21 04:18:37', '2014-12-21 04:18:37', '<a href="http://www.spiritmama.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/2-3.png"><img class=" wp-image-80 size-medium alignleft" src="http://www.spiritmama.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/2-3-300x251.png" alt="2 (3)" width="300" height="251" /></a>Holiday time here in Byron can be pretty full on. We have a massive influx of visitors and with the additional festivals going on, there are people everywhere. I''m quite a sensitive person by nature and I pick up on others energy like a sponge. The other day was one of those high energy, stressful rainy broken umbrella mornings. I encountered road rage and to add this to the mix, Indi was screaming in the back and no amount of songs or peanut butter sandwiches would suffice (in hindsight she was picking up on my rising stress levels)\r\n\r\nAs my grip tightened on the steering wheel, that small voice in my head was like ''calm down, breath''. I instinctively knew I was creating this cortisol rush and things were only going to escalate if I didn''t snap out of it. So, this is how I got right to changing my energy..\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Breath. Relax your body (obvious I know), unclench your jaw, unclench your hands on the steering wheel or pram and possibly unclench those butt cheeksJ</li>\r\n	<li>Watch your thoughts. Stop the merry go round of ''I’m so stressed out to day'', ''it’s so freaking busy'' etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Get Positive. Go through your gratitude list and look for things to be positive about. Mine went something like this ''how cute was Ollie today when he wanted to hold my hand as we walked into day care'' or ''look at those little bubby feet, Indi you''re so cute'' or ''so awesome I got a walk in today!''...you get the drift.</li>\r\n	<li>Music. If you''re in the car, crank some tunes, start singing, dancing, air punching whatever! The kids will love it!</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nMost important of all, see this experience as a sign to SLOW DOWN. There is always a greater force at work here and for some reason you’re stuck or held up. Have faith that this is where you are meant to be right here, right now.\r\n\r\nMiraculously this all worked for me. With my energy lighter and calmer, I got a rock star car park, shopping was a breeze and Indi was a dream, all done and dusted. Amazing what changing up your energy can do for the rest of your day.\r\n\r\nSo tell me mama, how have you snapped out of stress quickly with the kids?\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.spiritmama.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/signature.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-68" src="http://www.spiritmama.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/signature.png" alt="signature" width="171" height="53" /></a>', '4 Ways to Snap out of Stress', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '78', '', '', '2015-07-22 04:07:45', '2015-07-22 04:07:45', '', 0, 'http://www.spiritmama.com.au/?p=78', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(79, 1, '2015-07-21 04:15:21', '2015-07-21 04:15:21', 'It’s been a month now since my last breastfeed. Well I couldn''t even call it a feed; there wasn''t much in it for her. But it was a decision I put a lot of stress on myself over. Dreading the pangs of missing that close bond and interaction, feeling teary at the sight of seeing another mum and bub in that close embrace. As her feeds dropped<a href="http://www.spiritmama.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/1.png"><img class="alignright wp-image-75 size-medium" src="http://www.spiritmama.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/1-300x251.png" alt="1" width="300" height="251" /></a> one by one I really made an effort to enjoy every feed, be present with her and soak up the experience as much as I could. Here are somethings they <u>don’t </u>tell you that happen when you finish breastfeeding;\n<ul>\n	<li>You get quite hormonal for like 4 frickin weeks</li>\n	<li>It takes about 6 weeks for your boobs to ‘go down’</li>\n	<li>You may be a smaller bra size than what you were before you got pregnant and some lucky ones and go up!</li>\n	<li>Your boobs will be a bit saggy so you’ll probably never want to go braless or topless again.</li>\n	<li>You may stare a bit too long at kid free women and think “how are they so high and perky?”</li>\n	<li>You do feel a bit more ‘normal’ or more like your old self again (just an older, more tired version)</li>\n</ul>\nYou know what? Once it was done, I didn’t really look back. I do wish things could have been different breastfeeding Indi this time around but things are what they are. There''s always more to look forward to..new ''non-maternity'' bras with skinny straps!, new swimmers and tops that don’t need instant boob access..\n\nSo all in all, yes I miss that closeness we shared while breastfeeding but I will cherish what we had and keep those memories close to my heart.', '', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '74-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-07-21 04:15:21', '2015-07-21 04:15:21', '', 74, 'http://www.spiritmama.com.au/?p=79', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
