(88, 1, '2015-07-21 04:23:26', '2015-07-21 04:23:26', 'Holiday time here in Byron can be pretty full on. We have a massive influx of visitors and with the additional festivals going on, there are people everywhere. I''m quite a sensitive person by nature and I pick up on others energy like a sponge. The other day was one of those high energy, stressful rainy broken umbrella mornings. I encountered road rage and to add this to the mix, Indi was screaming in the back and no amount of songs or peanut butter sand<img class=" size-medium wp-image-80 alignleft" src="http://www.spiritmama.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/2-3-300x251.png" alt="2 (3)" width="300" height="251" />wiches would suffice (in hindsight she was picking up on my rising stress levels)\r\n\r\nAs my grip tightened on the steering wheel, that small voice in my head was like ''calm down, breath''. I instinctively knew I was creating this cortisol rush and things were only going to escalate if I didn''t snap out of it. So, this is how I got right to changing my energy..\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Breath. Relax your body (obvious I know), unclench your jaw, unclench your hands on the steering wheel or pram and possibly unclench those butt cheeks</li>\r\n	<li>Watch your thoughts. Stop the merry go round of ''I’m so stressed out to day'', ''it’s so freaking busy'' etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Get Positive. Go through your gratitude list and look for things to be positive about. Mine went something like this ''how cute was Ollie today when he wanted to hold my hand as we walked into day care'' or ''look at those little bubby feet, Indi you''re so cute'' or ''so awesome I got a walk in today!''...you get the drift.</li>\r\n	<li>Music. If you''re in the car, crank some tunes, start singing, dancing, air punching whatever! The kids will love it!</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nMost important of all, see this experience as a sign to SLOW DOWN. There is always a greater force at work here and for some reason you’re stuck or held up. Have faith that this is where you are meant to be right here, right now.\r\n\r\nMiraculously this all worked for me. With my energy lighter and calmer, I got a rock star car park, shopping was a breeze and Indi was a dream, all done and dusted. Amazing what changing up your energy can do for the rest of your day.\r\n\r\nSo tell me mama, how have you snapped out of stress quickly with the kids?<img class=" size-full wp-image-68 alignleft" src="http://www.spiritmama.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/signature.png" alt="signature" width="171" height="53" />', '4 Ways to Snap out of Stress', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '78-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-21 04:23:26', '2015-07-21 04:23:26', '', 78, 'http://www.spiritmama.com.au/?p=88', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
